\details{
Reads a delegator's staking state and history, and delegates or undelegates
the native token to or from a validator. Hyperliquid uses delegated
proof-of-stake: stake is delegated to validators, delegations carry a one-day
lockup, and rewards accrue every minute and compound daily.

Inherits from \link{HyperliquidBase}. All methods support both synchronous and
asynchronous execution depending on the \code{async} argument at construction.
\subsection{Purpose}{

Surface the staking account: the staked / free balances and pending
withdrawals (\link[=HyperliquidStaking]{get_staking_summary()}), the active
per-validator delegations (\link[=HyperliquidStaking]{get_staking_delegations()}),
the reward accrual history (\link[=HyperliquidStaking]{get_staking_rewards()}), the
full delegate/deposit/withdraw event ledger
(\link[=HyperliquidStaking]{get_delegator_history()}), and the delegate /
undelegate action itself (\link[=HyperliquidStaking]{token_delegate()}).
}

\subsection{Official Documentation}{

\url{https://hyperliquid.gitbook.io/hyperliquid-docs/hypercore/staking}
}

\subsection{Default address}{

The read methods default \code{address} to the instance's acting address
(vault, then master account, then the key's own wallet). Pass \code{address}
explicitly to inspect any other delegator.
}

